From a109ea09733a1f3d1cc0abb839717e6a8099876c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium Build <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 07:44:53 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 08/14] chronium: hardwareConcurrency + deviceMemory +
 maxTouchPoints + Battery + WebRTC
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Bundles four small but high-value spoofs on shared infra. Each is
independently checkable.

Hardware (NavigatorConcurrentHardware, NavigatorDeviceMemory,
NavigatorEvents::maxTouchPoints): per-profile hardware_concurrency,
device_memory, and max_touch_points override the host machine's
values when the corresponding HardwareFp is set in
blink::FingerprintState. Stops the fingerprinter from learning that
'the browser claims to be a 4-core Intel laptop but the CPU reports
28 logical cores' (the kind of cross-vector inconsistency Google
flags).

Battery (BatteryManager 4 methods): level/charging/chargingTime/
dischargingTime now come from the profile. negative charging_time /
discharging_time map to Infinity per spec when the device is at the
respective extreme.

WebRTC IP leak (peer_connection_dependency_factory): when
FingerprintState carries a non-default policy (1=proxy_only,
2=public_only), we set port_config.enable_multiple_routes=false,
enable_default_local_candidate=false, and enable_nonproxied_udp=
false (proxy_only) before the existing Platform routing-preferences
path can populate anything. This is the patch §5 #8 'WebRTC IP
leak' fix — the LAN address simply cannot appear in ICE candidates
because the underlying network manager isn't told to enumerate
those interfaces.

Plumbing (same pattern as patches 0006/0007): 4 new chrome_switches
(kFingerprintHardware, kFingerprintBattery, kFingerprintWebRtcPolicy,
plus the existing kFingerprintScreen lane), 3 new
FingerprintProfile CSV serialisers, 3 new FingerprintState struct
storages + setters/getters. WebRTC policy is a simple atomic<int>.

Verified on profile B:
  navigator.hardwareConcurrency : 4
  navigator.deviceMemory        : 4 (requires SecureContext, tested
                                     on https://example.com)
  navigator.maxTouchPoints      : 5
  navigator.getBattery()        : level 0.87, charging true,
                                  chargingTime/dischargingTime
                                  Infinity (matches JSON)

